      <header>&amp;cSkills!&amp;n</header>
      <slot>3</slot>
      <level>210</level>
      <author>210638</author>
      <date>1052047219</date>
      <authorname>Amarinda</authorname>
      <text>This guild now has a full set of gskills. That's right, the full amount
allowed by law. If you take a look at your scoresheet, you'll even find
a few bonuses. First, let me say that I've listed below who gets what
and why, along with updating this information in the ghelps.

Basic changes: Fine was dropped. It had zero code benefits for the most
part. It was a great idea in the concept, but it wasn't that great for
the actual MUD and how we operate. You will also see two new skills that
some of you may not have seen before - Arrogance and Offend. These are
two skills that used to be hunter gskills but were dumped when they put
in a brand new complete set of skills some few months back. In addition
to this, I have moved the good skills from Two Rivers to here - Medicine,
Stubborness, and Survival. Survival was dropped as it was a perfect copy
of Supply. This doesn't mean that all of you have these skills, but they
are now part of the Nations guild.

Commoners: You will receive Supply, Throw, Stubborness, Tail, Medicine,
and Offend. If you are a commoner and not a channie and do not see the
Stubborness listed on your sheet, it is because this skill cannot be
doubled or given if you are part of other major guilds.

Guards/Militia: You will receive Supply, Throw, Stubborness, Tail,
Armscry and Arrest. Just as with commoners, you may or may not have hte
Stubborness skill.

Nobility: You will receive Supply, Throw, Stubborness, Offend and
Arrogance. Just as with the commoners, you might or might not have the
Stubborness skill.

You can find the exact information under the ghelp files as to what
the different skills do. I regret that Stubborness has to have the
bit of a flaw that you can't have it when in other major guilds, but
there are a lot of other bonuses as a whole. The best part is that
there isn't anything else to worry about. You don't have to drag ass
to a GL about it unless you want to discuss the changes, you don't
have to convince someone that the skills need to be changed if you
are on when I'm not, and there is no hassle. The skills are there
for you to play with, all shiney new for ya.

Some of you are channies so there won't be Nations gskills showing on
your sheet. As well, some of you belong to other major guilds an have
maxed the limit of gskills. I did not take any skills from any of the
other guilds and if you had a free spot, I put in the most apt to be
of benefit to you. Most people didn't have their gskills set at their
approved limit, either. This means that some had supply at 83% or some
such. I changed all the gskills that I found to 100% as that is the
limit for their setting. I'm sure that I might have missed some, as I
am aware that I am most certainly not perfect. If you notice that one
or several of your gskills are below 100, feel free to ask to have
them brought up to the max. 

I think that covers it. I'm around if you want to ask questions about
them or whatnot. I encourage you to play with them and report back.
Oh, and one thing, be careful who you offend. *wink*
</text>
