      <text>I want to take a second and explain that if you sponsor someone, you are
stating that you have roleplayed with this character and find the person
able to RP this specific character. I'd rather give everyone sponsorship
rights but if I catch you sponsoring just because someone is your friend,
you will lose the ability. I tell most all newbies that they need a small
number of sponsors but I need RP logs of the RP. So.. let it be known that
if you sponsor and there's no RP log, it won't count as a sponsor for the
person that you're trying to help out. We need to know people are capable,
especially in a guild where there is no regulation. The guild depends on
you. Don't let it down.

&amp;r-&amp;wAma&amp;n
</text>
